column5: Got out this morning and between the 2 of us we bagged 8 nice mallards.....and my trusty dog Tundra is doing VERY well retrieving (still in training as she's only 4 months old today).

Nice shootin BB! But I gotta ask, did you guys drop something off the tailgate of the truck, cause the ducks are all lookin at what ever it was!!! HH  Edit... I looked again it it appears as though you guys didn't share the muffin with the ducks!
nice haul...  the pup seems to be doing well... i love the shots of the pup carrying the duck  cant wait for my brother to shoot some ducks... i wanna cook some up...
Looks like someone's having duck soup tonight!
Looks like buddy in the second picture ate a bowl of grumpy
Ya, it does doesn't it....thought the same thing.
Nice birds. The pup looks pretty good too!
It kind of does look like a muffin wrapper but it's just a leaf.
MURDERER!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!                 just kidding  Tundra likes to cary them ducks, but does she like to give em back
She drops them on command....of course a dog cookie is her reward...
yer lookin pretty svelt there too.How many lbs are ya down now.
Now we know that Billy Bob has all his ducks in a row!  That guy didnt eat a bowl of grump, he was asking why Billy Bob was using his tail gate instead of his own.
Nope....both Tundra's did there job holding the ducks....
Right on Billy Bob!  Nice big mallards.  How ya gunna cook em?
Beautiful pup BB.  That young and a whole bird in it,s mouth. I start my off by chasing down cut offed wings to get the taste/feel of the feathers.   Nice shoot,n pard.
Nice shootin' Bob!! Way to get 'er done!!  S.
I did that last month with a goose wing during our early goose season.
:good:  If I know you, you have been giving those birds up there a good beating by now....is the season still going ?
